  "setup_instructions": "## Get a Cisco Meraki Dashboard API key\n\nMeraki uses a **per-user API key** scoped to the organizations and networks that user can access. Best practice is to create a dedicated service account, not reuse your admin login.\n\n### 1. (Recommended) Create a service-account admin\n1. In **Meraki Dashboard**, go to **Organization → Configure → Administrators**.\n2. Click **Add admin**. Use an email you control (e.g. `meraki-svc@yourcompany.com`).\n3. Set **Organization access** to **Read-only** if T1 only needs visibility, or **Full** if you'll use it for response actions (blocking clients, isolating devices).\n4. Save. The admin will get an email to set their password — finish the signup.\n\n### 2. Enable the API for the organization\n1. **Organization → Settings**.\n2. Scroll to **Dashboard API access** and check **Enable access to the Cisco Meraki Dashboard API**.\n3. Save.\n\n### 3. Generate the API key\n1. Sign in to the Dashboard as the service-account admin.\n2. Click the profile avatar (top right) → **My profile**.\n3. Scroll to **API access** → click **Generate new API key**.\n4. Copy the key immediately — Meraki only shows it once. If lost, you must revoke and regenerate.\n\n### 4. Paste the key below\nPaste in the **API Key** field. T1 sends it as the `X-Cisco-Meraki-API-Key` request header automatically (and adds `Accept: application/json`).\n\nClick **Test Authentication** to confirm. The test calls `/organizations` and expects a 200 with at least one org.\n\n### Region matters\nMeraki has regional dashboards (`api.meraki.com`, `api.eu.meraki.com`, `api.cn.meraki.com`). T1 defaults to the global endpoint. If your org is hosted in EU/CN/IN, override the **Base URL** field to the matching regional host or all calls will 404.\n\n### Rate limits\n- **5 requests/second** per organization across all clients. T1 will retry with exponential backoff on 429 but bursty triage can still get throttled.\n\n### Troubleshooting\n- **`401 Invalid API key`**: Key wrong, revoked, or the admin was deleted.\n- **`403 Operation requires access`**: Your service admin doesn't have the right scope on the requested org/network. Promote in Dashboard Administrators.\n- **`404 Not Found`** on listing orgs: API access not enabled on the org. See step 2.\n- **All calls 404**: Wrong region — switch the Base URL.",
